<h4>Sizing the Table</h4>


<p>When you insert a table, it inserts at a preset, default size. If you want
to change the size of the table from the default, you can do so easily, let's
learn how.</p>

<p>You size the table the same way in all the versions.</p>


<p>Move the cursor to the top left-hand corner of the table (circled in the
picture) and click on the + that appears to select the table.</p>

<p>Click and drag on the bounding box, or sizing box that appears (circled in
the picture) in the bottom right-hand corner to size the table.</p>

<img class="img-wrap style1" src=
            "images/wordprocessing/sizingtables.jpg" alt="">

<br>

<p>In the picture below, you can see that the table has been sized to make the
two columns narrower and the two rows wider.</p>

<img class="img-wrap style1" src=
            "images/wordprocessing/sizingtableresults.jpg" alt="">
<br>
<p>If you want to change the text alignment inside the table, add borders or
shading, or change other details, you can so do using Table Properties.</p>

</div>
