<h4>Table Properties</h4>



<p>Right click on the top left-hand corner on the + (circled in the picture)
and click on Table Properties (boxed in the picture) from the menu that
appears.</p>

<img class="img-wrap style1" src=
            "images/wordprocessing/tableproperties.jpg" alt="">
<hr>

<p>In the Table Properties Option Box, notice the four tabs at the top. Each
tab allows you to customize the Table, the Row, the Column or a Cell. A <strong>cell</strong> is
an individual part of either a column or a row. Notice you can adjust the alignment of the data you place within the cell under the Alignment section.</p>

